            "bio": "Israel Davidson (1870–1939), born in Jonava, Lithuania, was a Jewish American scholar and publisher. He has been recognized as one of the leading American Hebrew writers in his era. His magnum opus was the four volume <em>Otsar ha-shirah veha-piyut</em> (Thesaurus of Mediaeval Hebrew Poetry; New York: 1924–1933). Davidson studied in yeshivas in Jonava, Volozhin, and Slobodka. In 1898, he immigrated to New York, worked at a few occupations before earning a Ph.D. from Columbia University.",
