    "excerpt": "By a 16th century paytan named Yitsḥaq, this is a Purim parody of the Havdalah (and Yom Kippur) piyyuṭ \"HaMavdil,\" found in Israel Davidson's classic work <em>Parody in Jewish Literature</em> (1907), pp. 36-37. . . .",
    "content": "<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\nA parody of the Havdalah (and Yom Kippur) piyyuṭ HaMavdil for Purim from the 16th century, found in Israel Davidson&#8217;s classic work <em>Parody in Jewish Literature</em> (1907). Despite the acrostic signature, I didn&#8217;t write it I swear!\n</div>\n<hr />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Rhyming Translation (English, Davidson 1907)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nהַמַּבְדִּיל בֵּין־כִּפּוּר לְפוּרִים<br />\nשֶׁשּׂוֹנֵא אֶת־הַנְּזִירִים<br />\nוְאוֹהֵב אֶת־הַשִּׁכּוֹרִים<br />\nהַצּוֹעֲקִים בַּלָּֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay the One who distinguishes between Yom Kippur and Purim,<br />\nwho hates the nazirites<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Who are required to abstain from wine&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nand loves the drunkards<br />\nshouting all night…\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nHere&#8217;s to him who flings aside<br />\nThe cup of penitence at Purim tide,<br />\nAnd fees the hermits with drunkards to bide<br />\nHowling through the night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nיַֽׄיִן אָדֹם אָהַֽבְתִּי<br />\nוְגַם עִם־לָבָן גַּֽרְתִּי<br />\nוְשׁוֹתֶה מַֽיִם שָׂנֵֽאתִי<br />\nכָּאֲפֵלָה וּכְאִשּׁוֹן לָֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nRed wine I love,<br />\nbut I can live with white.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> A pun on Jacob’s statement (in Gen. 32:4) upon returning home, “I have lived with Lavan” — whose name literally means “white.”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nAnd drinking water I hate,<br />\nlike gloom and like the black of night.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nRed wine I prize as meed,<br />\nWhite wine is good in time of need,<br />\nBut the water-drinker I hate, indeed,<br />\nAs the dense darkness of the night;\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nצְׄעָקָה וּדְמָעוֹת אוֹרִֽידָה<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Printed: ירדה — emendation Davidson’s.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nבִּרְאוֹתִי מַֽיִם בִּסְעוּדָה<br />\nהָבִֽיאוּ לִי עֶשְׂרִים מִדָּה<br />\nאוּלַי יַסְפִּיקוּן לִי הַלָּֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nShouting, tears I shed<br />\nwhen I see water at a feast.<br />\nBring me twenty measures!<br />\nPerhaps that will be enough for me tonight.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI cry, and tears I shed<br />\nIf on water I am fed;<br />\nO, for twenty measures of sparkling red<br />\nTo quench my thirst to-night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nחֵׄן וָחֶֽסֶד יֻתַּן לָרָעִים<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Printed: להם — emendation Davidson’s.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nאִם־תּוֹסִֽיפוּ יַֽיִן בַּגְּבִיעִים<br />\nעִם־כּוֹסוֹת שֵׁכָר מְלֵאִים<br />\nאוּלַי נִשְׁכְּרָה זֶה הַלָּֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nGrace and mercy will be given to the wicked<br />\nif you increase wine in goblets along<br />\nwith full cups of liquor —<br />\nperhaps we will get drunk this very night.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nYour praise, my friends, aloud I&#8217;ll cry<br />\nIf ne&#8217;er the wine in my cup go dry.<br />\nWith brimful jugs of beer we&#8217;ll try<br />\nTo get drunk to-night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nקְׄדֻשָּׁה אֲלַמֶּדְכֶם<br />\nחֲכָמִים הַטּוּ אׇזְנְכֶם<br />\nבַּעֲרוּ מַֽיִם מִבָּתֵּיכֶם<br />\nכִּי הֵם חֲשׁוּבִים כַּלָּֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nHoliness I will teach you;<br />\nsages, incline your ears —<br />\nremove water from your homes,<br />\nfor it is considered like night!\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nA holy deed I teach you, hear!<br />\nMen of wisdom incline your ear!<br />\nKeep your houses of water clear,<br />\n&#8216;Tis as bad as the night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nחִׄזְׄקׄוּ נְבוֹנִים וַחֲכָמִים<br />\nבִּזְכוּת נֹחַ אִישׁ תָּמִים<br />\nאֲשֶׁר נָטַע כְּרָמִים<br />\nלְשִׁכְרוּת בַּיּוֹם וּבַלָּיְלָה׃׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nBe strong, scholars and sages,<br />\nin the merit of Noaḥ the upright man,<br />\nwho planted vineyards<br />\nto get drunk by day and by night.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nSummon courage men of lore<br />\nFor Noaḥ&#8217;s sake, the Righteous of yore,<br />\nWho planted vineyards, unknown before,<br />\nTo drink by day and night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>By a 16th century paytan named Yitsḥaq, this is a Purim parody of the Havdalah (and Yom Kippur) piyyuṭ &#8220;HaMavdil,&#8221; found in Israel Davidson&#8217;s <em>Parody in Jewish Literature</em> (1907), pp. 36-37.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<style>\n       .errordiv { padding:10px; margin:10px; border: 1px solid #555555;color: #000000;background-color: #f8f8f8; width:500px; }#advanced_iframe {visibility:visible;opacity:1;vertical-align:top;}.ai-info-bottom-iframe { position: fixed; z-index: 10000; bottom:0; left: 0; margin: 0px; text-align: center; width: 100%; background-color: #ff9999; padding-left: 5px;padding-bottom: 5px; border-top: 1px solid #aaa } a.ai-bold {font-weight: bold;}#ai-layer-div-advanced_iframe p {height:100%;margin:0;padding:0}#ai-div-container-advanced_iframe\n       {\n           position: relative;\n           width: 100%; max-width: 100%;}\n       #ai-div-loader-advanced_iframe\n       {\n          position: absolute;\n          z-index:1000;\n          margin-left:-33px;\n          left: 50%;   top: 150px;\n         }}\n       #ai-div-loader-advanced_iframe img\n       {\n          border: none;\n       }</style><script type=\"text/javascript\">var ai_ifr